itics charles perrow bloomberg news 2011 cover no need to reset the reset matthew rojansky the new york times 2011 cover exporting the norwegian model the effect of administrative design on oil sector performance mark c thurber david hults patrick rp heller energy policy 2011 cover america after the oil spill in the gulf of mexico roland benedikter berliner debatte zeitschrift fur sozialwissenschaftlichen diskurs vol 1 2011 cover on the state's choice of oil company risk management and the frontier of the petroleum industry peter a nolan mark c thurber program on energy and sustainable development 2010 cover nnpc and nigeria's oil patronage ecosystem mark c thurber ifeyinwa m emelife patrick rp heller program on energy and sustainable development 2010 cover no picnic the dynamics of culture in the contemporary arab world hicham ben abdallah le monde diplomatique 2010 cover scott sagan's introductory statement at the sagan payne debate on us nuclear declaratory policy on may 25 2010 scott sagan cisac 2010 cover gas & geopolitics the foreign policy implications of energy import dependency sam stone cisac 2010 previous records next records search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages topical news national oil companies can cause pain at pump research shows february 16 2012 pesd news charles perrow how technology can nudge climate change politics bloomberg view on october 23 2011 thurber hults heller publish norwegian model study in energy policy july 5 2011 pesd announcement nolan and thurber identify risk as a major driver of whether countries use private or state owned oil companies december 13 2010 pesd news pesd releases study of nigeria's national oil company nnpc september 10 2010 pesd announcement hicham ben abdallah cultural dynamics in the contemporary arab world fsi stanford cddrl in the news le monde diplomatique august 2010 in french on august 8 2010 more news about this topic support ma